You might get error with a &quot;transitive dependency&quot;.

MyJar1.jar

    public interface ICooler
    {
      public CoolerThing makeACooler(String x);
    
    }

..

MyJar2.jar

    public class CoolerThing
    {
    }


If your unit-test library tries to mock ICooler, it needs a reference to MyJar2.jar to be able to mock the method &quot;makeACooler&quot; because of the return type (or not shown input object type) of CoolerThing.


Note, your MyJar1 and MyJar2 may be &quot;groupid/artifactid&quot; items from public maven, (or private maven, or &quot;jfrog&quot;, etc, etc).

